A man who falsely claimed benefits under his brother's name for nearly three decades has been found living in a holiday resort on Spain's Costa del Sol.

Retired joiner Norman Brennan, 70, fled to Mijas from Britain five years ago just as he was due to be sentenced for embezzling almost £120,000 under the name of his brother who lived abroad.

Today, as Brennan said he would not return to face justice, Work and Pensions secretary Iain Duncan Smith said he would deal with the fugitive fraudster himself.

'This case is outrageous,' the politician said.

