Mr Duncan Smith told the news channel: 'I’m astonished. I’ll certainly take this case away, and I know that I have myself fraud investigators who are out in Spain already.

'We’ll check this case, and I can promise you that if they haven’t done enough, they will now do their level best to get this man back.

'This sort of case is outrageous, and I’ll deal with it.'

A spokesman for Merseyside Police said: 'Merseyside Police can confirm assistance was provided to Sefton Council and the Department for Work and Pensions (DWP) with their original investigation into Mr Brennan.

'Since the issue of an arrest warrant for Mr Brennan in 2008 the force has been working with other agencies to locate and affect his arrest. This work is ongoing.'

An international arrest warrant remains in place for Brennan.

